---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About BuildWorkPro – Construction Software for Subcontractors" description="BuildWorkPro was built to solve the construction software problem for subcontractors. Purpose-built for specialty trades, designed for real workflows.">
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">About us</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">
          We're building for the builders
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-slate-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
          Subcontractors are the backbone of the construction industry. They make up the majority of every jobsite, yet the software built for construction has always been designed for general contractors first.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate mx-auto">
        <h2>The problem we saw</h2>
        <p>
          Most construction management software charges hundreds of dollars per month, scales by user count, and buries the features that subs actually need — pay applications, change orders, and field documentation — behind enterprise tiers. Small and mid-size specialty contractors are left with spreadsheets, paper forms, and disconnected tools.
        </p>

        <h2>Our approach</h2>
        <p>
          BuildWorkPro is a subcontractor-first platform. Every feature is designed around how specialty trades actually work — from bidding jobs and tracking projects, to submitting pay apps and documenting the field. One plan, one price, everything included.
        </p>
        <p>
          We believe the plumber with a 5-person crew deserves the same quality tools as the GC running a $100M backlog. That's why we built BuildWorkPro at <strong>$79/month flat</strong> — no per-user fees, no feature gates, no surprises.
        </p>

        <h2>What we stand for</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Subs first.</strong> Every feature decision starts with "does this help a specialty contractor?"</li>
          <li><strong>Simple pricing.</strong> One plan, everything included. We don't penalize you for growing your team.</li>
          <li><strong>Built to be used.</strong> Clean, fast, and practical — not bloated with features nobody asked for.</li>
          <li><strong>Your data, your business.</strong> We don't sell your data. We sell software.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-16">
      <CTA />
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
